from django.shortcuts import get_list_or_404
from cloud.location.models import Address

def get_route(address_ids: list[UUID]) -> RouteResponse | None:
    # Get all addresses in one query, will raise 404 if any address is missing
    addresses = get_list_or_404(Address, id__in=address_ids)

    # Make sure addresses are in the same order as the input IDs
    address_map = {str(addr.id): addr for addr in addresses}
    ordered_addresses = [address_map[str(addr_id)] for addr_id in address_ids]

    return fetch_route(ordered_addresses)
```

Key points:

1. Using `get_list_or_404` ensures we get all addresses or return a 404 if any are missing
2. We maintain the order of addresses to match the input order (important for routes)
3. We do this in a single database query rather than multiple lookups

